Title: Object: I Re Dell' Egitto. (Egyptian rulers.)
Description: Portraits of seven Egyptian rulers, Abbas I at centre surrounded by Abbas II, Ishmail Pacha, Hébrahime, Moahamet, Said and Théophil Pacha, in ovals; ornate curtain surmounted by crown with crescent moon and star, two flags behind. Chromolithograph
Curator's comments: Published in the period when Elsass was part of Germany.
